In .NET MAUI Shell, you can override `OnBackButtonPressed` and use Shell navigation events:

```csharp
public partial class EditProductPage : ContentPage
{
    private bool _hasUnsavedChanges;

    public EditProductPage()
    {
        InitializeComponent();

        // Custom "Cancel" back button
        Shell.SetBackButtonBehavior(this, new BackButtonBehavior
        {
            Text = "Cancel",
            Command = new Command(async () => await TryNavigateBack())
        });
    }

    // Handles hardware/software back button (Android, etc.)
    protected override bool OnBackButtonPressed()
    {
        if (_hasUnsavedChanges)
        {
            MainThread.BeginInvokeOnMainThread(async () => await TryNavigateBack());
            return true; // Cancel default navigation
        }
        return base.OnBackButtonPressed();
    }

    private async Task TryNavigateBack()
    {
        if (_hasUnsavedChanges)
        {
            bool leave = await DisplayAlert(
                "Unsaved Changes",
                "You have unsaved changes. Discard and go back?",
                "Discard", "Stay");

            if (!leave) return; // User chose to stay
        }

        await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
    }
}
```

**Key points:**

- **`BackButtonBehavior`** — customizes the Shell toolbar back button (text, icon, command).
- **`OnBackButtonPressed`** — intercepts the Android/device back button. Return `true` to cancel navigation.
- **`DisplayAlert`** — shows the confirmation dialog.
- Navigate with `GoToAsync("..")` only after the user confirms.

> ⚠️ Shell's `Navigating` event supports `e.Cancel()` but only on some platforms. The pattern above is more reliable cross-platform.
